1
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:34,640
At his age, he doesn't need to work.
Just sit around, and that's it.

2
00:00:34,640 --> 00:00:38,200
Right. He can barely even walk now.

3
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:40,880
You can go now.
We've come as far as we can.

4
00:01:10,250 --> 00:01:11,760
Hmph.

5
00:01:16,790 --> 00:01:17,860
Come on now.

6
00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:38,320
Your friend still not talking?

7
00:01:56,270 --> 00:02:00,180
Grandpa, are you good now?
I'm sleepy.

8
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:02,040
Aw.

9
00:02:02,980 --> 00:02:04,480
Then go to bed, Snow.

10
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:08,160
Okay.

11
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:24,960
Ow...

12
00:02:26,300 --> 00:02:27,300
Ow.

13
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:49,760
Huh.

14
00:03:46,220 --> 00:03:47,400
Ugh.

15
00:03:47,430 --> 00:03:48,430
Ouch...

16
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:53,200
Oow.

17
00:03:55,250 --> 00:03:56,320
Ow. Ugh.

18
00:04:11,930 --> 00:04:13,440
Father's still not up?

19
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,000
Father.

20
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:19,400
You awake?

21
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:21,480
Yeah, I'm up.

22
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,240
Oh? Father.

23
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:37,160
Are you okay?

24
00:04:40,170 --> 00:04:41,170
I'm fine.

25
00:04:41,190 --> 00:04:43,920
I just...knocked it with my hand.

26
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:46,200
What about you? Anything wrong?

27
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:47,400
Everything is all right.

28
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:50,720
I thought it was odd
that you weren't up yet.

29
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:51,920
Oh, yeah, yeah.

30
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:56,030
- I was just about to get up.
- Okay.

31
00:04:57,110 --> 00:04:59,960
Father. Oh...hmph.

32
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:07,400
Tell me where it hurts.

33
00:05:09,840 --> 00:05:11,200
It's not that bad.

34
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:13,720
Don't tough it out, Grandpa.

35
00:05:14,330 --> 00:05:16,570
Tell me so I'll work
on the right spots.

36
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:18,600
My whole back is killing me.

37
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:20,900
Not just his back.

38
00:05:21,570 --> 00:05:23,790
Last night, he had me massage
his shoulders too.

39
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:25,600
There you go.

40
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:29,880
So where exactly does it hurt?
All of it.

41
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:34,040
You always tell me
not to be difficult. Now you.

42
00:05:34,220 --> 00:05:36,600
Fine. Everything hurts.

43
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:41,280
Elbow, shoulder,
the muscles, the arms...

44
00:05:43,270 --> 00:05:44,270
Let me see.

45
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:45,840
- Oh, wow.
- Oh?

46
00:05:50,420 --> 00:05:51,420
- Dad.
- Hmm?

47
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:53,800
It's getting serious.
Let's go to a doctor.

48
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:58,120
No, some balm and a massage will do.

49
00:05:59,230 --> 00:06:01,460
Then let's rub the balm on now.

50
00:06:01,710 --> 00:06:04,160
If it doesn't get better,
I'll take you myself.

51
00:06:07,990 --> 00:06:10,350
Hmm? What is it, Father?

52
00:06:10,950 --> 00:06:15,080
Your back brace. You done with it?
Let me use it.

53
00:06:15,110 --> 00:06:16,960
Oh, Father.

54
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:18,510
What, Grandpa?

55
00:06:18,850 --> 00:06:21,920
You're just catching up
with the office syndrome trend.

56
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,400
Come here. Let me massage you.

57
00:06:27,230 --> 00:06:28,280
Easy now.

58
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:31,040
Gentle, son. Light pressure.
Not too hard.

59
00:06:31,070 --> 00:06:32,440
Okay, okay.
Nice and easy.

60
00:06:32,660 --> 00:06:33,690
Okay, Dad.

61
00:06:34,790 --> 00:06:35,790
Ooh.

62
00:06:57,190 --> 00:06:58,190
Hey, Pipe.

63
00:07:00,930 --> 00:07:02,920
Yeah, Phi Save?
Wanna play with my doll?

64
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:08,480
No.

65
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:10,560
I'm here to trade.

66
00:07:11,970 --> 00:07:14,600
This one...is a secret character.

67
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:19,640
And this one...is super rare.

68
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,000
I'll give you two for it.

69
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:25,680
Trade for this one. Deal?

70
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:30,080
Sure, Phi Save.
Two-for-one is always a super.

71
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:36,480
Hmm? A massage balm?
It reeks.

72
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:40,800
Yo, boys. New toys.

73
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:42,160
What is it?

74
00:07:42,180 --> 00:07:43,860
- Let me see.
- Let me see.

75
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:44,880
So cool.

76
00:07:44,910 --> 00:07:45,910
Awesome.

77
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:01,480
"Got what you gave me."

78
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:03,680
"It's so cute. Thanks a lot."

79
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:15,430
"Unread message"

80
00:08:34,550 --> 00:08:37,320
Well, well...

81
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,320
What?

82
00:08:39,040 --> 00:08:41,840
Don't let me catch you
sneaking up to write.

83
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:43,070
- Hmm?
- Hehe.

84
00:08:43,490 --> 00:08:47,640
- I'm awake. Hehe.
- Hmph...back in there.

85
00:08:49,070 --> 00:08:50,440
Just rest, okay?

86
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:54,880
So? You patched things up
with him yet?

87
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:01,560
Sounds like he's cut you
out of his life.

88
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:03,440
Think so?

89
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:04,440
Well,...

90
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:06,920
you went at him pretty hard first.

91
00:09:09,190 --> 00:09:10,190
Yeah.

92
00:09:10,870 --> 00:09:12,050
I messed up. I know.

93
00:09:12,420 --> 00:09:14,440
Oh-ho. Ho.

94
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:16,440
Look at you.

95
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:19,280
It took you long enough

96
00:09:19,640 --> 00:09:23,320
to admit you were wrong, huh?

97
00:09:23,950 --> 00:09:26,880
That big ego?
I must have gotten it from you.

98
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:31,400
Then how about
trying a little harder?

99
00:09:33,830 --> 00:09:34,830
Like how?

100
00:09:36,930 --> 00:09:37,930
Make him something.

101
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:39,880
Handmade.

102
00:09:39,910 --> 00:09:43,270
Correct. Hey, a story for ya.

103
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:45,360
I once made a friend angry.

104
00:09:45,680 --> 00:09:48,200
I made something for him.

105
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:51,280
It's a gun box. He was into guns.

106
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:55,040
The moment he saw it,
he lit right up.

107
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:56,780
Ah-ha.

108
00:09:57,730 --> 00:10:00,180
But...I don't know
how to make anything.

109
00:10:01,220 --> 00:10:03,180
- Can I just buy something?
- No.

110
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:05,090
When you make it yourself,

111
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:09,080
he'll see how much
you really mean it.

112
00:10:09,350 --> 00:10:11,160
And the harder it is to make,

113
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:16,480
the more he'll know
you're truly sorry.

114
00:10:18,430 --> 00:10:19,430
Got it, Grandpa.

115
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:25,320
Thanks so much. I'll be back.

116
00:10:25,340 --> 00:10:26,630
Yeah...

117
00:10:26,650 --> 00:10:27,800
You rest.

118
00:10:28,770 --> 00:10:31,680
Hmm...rest, okay? I'll be back.

119
00:11:06,460 --> 00:11:09,880
"'Geez, how can I
make peace with Nan now?'"

120
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:15,720
"He mutters and vents
to the empty room."

121
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:18,480
"'I shouldn't have run
my mouth like that.'"

122
00:11:18,700 --> 00:11:21,340
"The young man
going back and forth,"

123
00:11:21,450 --> 00:11:23,920
"thinking of a way to
make things right with his friend."

124
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:28,160
"He hopes to restore the friendship,
the way it used to be."

125
00:11:31,580 --> 00:11:33,440
"DIY gift, hardest to make"

126
00:11:39,410 --> 00:11:40,550
Knitting.

127
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:48,770
"Easiest knit craft"

128
00:11:50,030 --> 00:11:51,030
No, no. Wrong.

129
00:11:54,220 --> 00:11:55,920
What is the...

130
00:11:57,010 --> 00:11:59,280
hardest thing to knit?

131
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:03,880
Knit a sweater.

132
00:12:04,860 --> 00:12:05,860
Let's do it.

133
00:12:06,970 --> 00:12:08,000
Huh.

134
00:12:15,130 --> 00:12:16,480
- There you are.
- Ah.

135
00:12:16,510 --> 00:12:18,230
Up writing again.

136
00:12:19,050 --> 00:12:23,520
Well...the pain's gone.
How can I just lie here?

137
00:12:23,550 --> 00:12:27,610
That's enough, Dad.
Come here. Get up. Let's go.

138
00:12:27,640 --> 00:12:29,740
Ow, ow, ow...

139
00:12:29,770 --> 00:12:31,320
You said the pain's gone.

140
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:33,960
It's back
because you're carrying me.

141
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:37,000
Come on, come on. Easy.

142
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:38,760
No writing. Enough is enough.

143
00:12:38,790 --> 00:12:39,760
Don't squeeze my arm.

144
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:42,440
Oh, sorry, sorry.

145
00:12:42,590 --> 00:12:45,280
Sorry. Come on, come on.

146
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:49,440
Easy. Here, sit down.

147
00:12:50,140 --> 00:12:53,060
Okay. Watch your back and lie down.

148
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,760
Ow, ow, ow...

149
00:12:55,780 --> 00:12:58,360
- My legs. My legs.
- Okay, got it, got it.

150
00:12:58,790 --> 00:13:02,120
Lie down, Dad.
See, all curled up like a shrimp.

151
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:07,200
- Alright, now. Rest, really, Dad.
- Yeah.

152
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:08,560
Okay.

153
00:13:14,660 --> 00:13:15,840
Whatchu doing?

154
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:18,480
Hey, where are you taking that?

155
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:19,920
I'm putting this away.

156
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:22,440
You don't need to. I won't write.

157
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:26,760
I don't believe you.
Let me hold onto it.

158
00:13:26,830 --> 00:13:28,240
When will I get it back?

159
00:13:28,270 --> 00:13:31,800
After you recover. Now, rest.

160
00:13:31,820 --> 00:13:32,360
Sorn.

161
00:13:32,390 --> 00:13:34,570
- I'll hold onto it. Bye.
- Sorn. Sorn.

162
00:13:34,590 --> 00:13:35,590
Sorn.

163
00:13:35,810 --> 00:13:38,400
Sorn. Oh-ho, ow.

164
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:43,960
I was just on a roll. Dang it.

165
00:13:47,970 --> 00:13:49,400
Here, Pheem, take it. Ready?

166
00:13:49,650 --> 00:13:50,810
- Hey, guys.
- You in, Messi?

167
00:13:53,130 --> 00:13:54,240
I'm not playing today.

168
00:13:56,130 --> 00:13:57,130
Oh?

169
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:00,290
- What's wrong with him?
- Yeah.

170
00:14:01,740 --> 00:14:02,920
- Hey.
- Oh, another one.

171
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:06,880
Guy, I'm sorry.

172
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:19,040
I'm sorry.
What I said was out of line.

173
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:21,010
You actually know that?

174
00:14:21,280 --> 00:14:22,550
I got frustrated with Grandpa,

175
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:24,680
and I took it out on you.

176
00:14:25,300 --> 00:14:26,720
Just as I thought.

177
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:29,080
That was on me.

178
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:31,520
I own it.

179
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:35,040
You know? Some things, once said,
cannot be taken back.

180
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:38,360
I know.

181
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:42,080
You said
we came as far as we could.

182
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:43,800
Then, we are no more.

183
00:14:45,470 --> 00:14:46,470
Guy.

184
00:14:50,770 --> 00:14:51,770
Ow.

185
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:59,280
I'm fine. Just go.

186
00:15:04,040 --> 00:15:05,040
Ow.

187
00:15:05,790 --> 00:15:07,680
Save, you idiot.

188
00:15:13,940 --> 00:15:15,680
A kick that hard
probably broke a toe.

189
00:15:19,980 --> 00:15:21,280
You still mad at me?

190
00:15:21,430 --> 00:15:22,430
Yeah.

191
00:15:24,170 --> 00:15:25,170
Can you get up?

192
00:15:26,530 --> 00:15:27,530
Yeah.

193
00:15:57,510 --> 00:15:58,640
Thanks, man.

194
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:32,440
Take it off.
What?

195
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:35,280
Your shoe. Take it off.

196
00:16:40,430 --> 00:16:41,430
Ugh.

197
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:46,840
That toe must come off.

198
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:48,560
What? Are you serious?

199
00:16:48,740 --> 00:16:50,440
You believed that? Silly.

200
00:16:56,370 --> 00:16:57,860
Aren't you waiting
for the teacher?

201
00:16:59,180 --> 00:17:00,560
Easy. I can handle it.

202
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:31,520
Whatchu doing?

203
00:17:31,650 --> 00:17:32,840
Uh...

204
00:17:34,280 --> 00:17:35,280
I'm just...

205
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:36,720
exercising my hand.

206
00:17:43,170 --> 00:17:44,800
Oh-oh. Easy, easy.

207
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:48,400
Ugh...

208
00:18:05,040 --> 00:18:06,040
Oh-oh.

209
00:18:07,190 --> 00:18:08,190
Easy.

210
00:18:39,420 --> 00:18:40,640
Thanks a lot.

211
00:18:41,860 --> 00:18:42,860
Yeah.

212
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:47,800
- Phi Sorn.
- Hmm?

213
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:49,570
Save says the channel's back.

214
00:18:49,570 --> 00:18:51,200
Oh, really? Let me see.

215
00:18:52,780 --> 00:18:54,200
Okay. Let me look.

216
00:18:54,540 --> 00:18:56,400
Hey, it's actually back.

217
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:57,820
"Sanae Chan by Auntie Mart"

218
00:18:57,820 --> 00:18:58,260
Good.

219
00:18:58,280 --> 00:19:00,360
Should we do a livestream then?

220
00:19:01,770 --> 00:19:04,370
We can't do it ourselves.
We already tried that.

221
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:06,440
That's true.

222
00:19:07,960 --> 00:19:09,960
And Guy, my boy,
isn't coming anymore.

223
00:19:10,560 --> 00:19:13,280
"My boy"?
Since when is he your child?

224
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:16,640
This is on you.
You didn't want him coming.

225
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:18,360
Got what you want, huh?

226
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:22,400
Hey, I've got an idea.

227
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:26,040
- Hello.
- Hi, hi.

228
00:19:26,620 --> 00:19:30,000
Ma'am, these are Sanae Chan sweets
by Auntie Mart.

229
00:19:30,100 --> 00:19:32,160
They're good. Watch, watch.

230
00:19:33,040 --> 00:19:34,600
Hoo.

231
00:19:34,620 --> 00:19:36,280
- Look amazing, let me try.
- Soft and chewy.

232
00:19:36,310 --> 00:19:37,590
Of course.

233
00:19:38,040 --> 00:19:39,920
Watch me, watch.

234
00:19:39,920 --> 00:19:41,280
Oh wow, they're really good.

235
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:42,880
Made from mochi flour.

236
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:46,280
Not too sweet.
Healthy-delicious.

237
00:19:47,240 --> 00:19:48,600
Click, pay, done.

238
00:19:48,900 --> 00:19:50,760
Click, click, click now.

239
00:19:50,780 --> 00:19:51,980
Click away...

240
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:57,960
Well? Is my idea working?

241
00:19:57,960 --> 00:20:00,040
Hehe.

242
00:20:00,340 --> 00:20:03,300
Well, well. Snow could do this too.

243
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:05,320
Why did you say that?

244
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:08,920
All she does is dance all day.
She never reads anything,

245
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:11,880
except those BL novels.

246
00:20:12,580 --> 00:20:18,060
See? This might just be
our daughter's special talent.

247
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:21,840
Today, we also have
a dance performance.

248
00:20:22,240 --> 00:20:24,360
3, 2, 1.

249
00:20:24,360 --> 00:20:27,800
Sanae Chan sweets by Auntie Mart.

250
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:30,650
Sanae Chan sweets by Aunt Mart.

251
00:20:30,810 --> 00:20:33,540
Sanae Chan sweets by Aunt Mart.

252
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:36,600
Sanae Chan sweets by Aunt Mart.

253
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:40,840
Ow, ow, ow.

254
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,240
Ow.

255
00:20:49,500 --> 00:20:50,500
Grandpa.

256
00:20:50,530 --> 00:20:51,530
Ow.

257
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:54,720
What happened to your foot?

258
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:56,400
I came to tell you something.

259
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:04,960
Guy still won't forgive me.

260
00:21:05,360 --> 00:21:10,920
Just wait. He's still hot.
Try again after he cools down.

261
00:21:11,960 --> 00:21:13,240
Will that day even come?

262
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:15,880
Let me ask you.

263
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:21,320
Do you want to make up with Guy
because you need him for the novel,

264
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:22,180
or because you...

265
00:21:22,180 --> 00:21:25,560
can't stand the thought of him
not being in your life?

266
00:21:46,650 --> 00:21:48,040
Your novel or not,

267
00:21:48,350 --> 00:21:50,420
he's someone I want to keep around.

268
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:53,320
That means you care about Guy a lot.

269
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:54,880
Care? No way.

270
00:21:55,030 --> 00:21:59,120
Your story's got my hands itching.

271
00:21:59,140 --> 00:22:01,140
I really want to
get back to writing.

272
00:22:01,170 --> 00:22:04,600
Right now, you need rest.
Or your back will get worse.

273
00:22:04,690 --> 00:22:08,170
But the ideas are flooding my head.

274
00:22:09,240 --> 00:22:12,480
You have to take care of your body.

275
00:22:12,740 --> 00:22:13,910
For a writer like you,

276
00:22:14,260 --> 00:22:18,920
your fingers, wrists,
arms, back, and shoulders

277
00:22:19,740 --> 00:22:21,800
do need your attention.
You know that?

278
00:22:22,380 --> 00:22:24,280
They're your bread and butter.

279
00:22:24,410 --> 00:22:25,970
- Yeah, look at that.
- Ouch.

280
00:22:25,990 --> 00:22:26,730
Haha.

281
00:22:26,750 --> 00:22:29,720
Coming from the guy
who just kicked a tree.

282
00:22:30,430 --> 00:22:33,440
Come on, Grandpa. Trust me on this.

283
00:22:33,840 --> 00:22:37,320
Some manga artists
push themselves so hard

284
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:39,340
they have to take a year off.

285
00:22:39,960 --> 00:22:42,280
Take care of yourself,
then get back on the novel.

286
00:22:45,460 --> 00:22:48,180
Getting old. Everything's a hassle.

287
00:22:49,750 --> 00:22:52,660
Have you tried this app
on your phone?

288
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:54,920
You just speak
and it writes for you.

289
00:22:55,360 --> 00:22:58,160
No. I like reading
my own handwriting.

290
00:22:58,760 --> 00:23:01,760
What about recording?
You can capture a lot of ideas.

291
00:23:01,970 --> 00:23:04,360
No. Can't go back
and edit a recording.

292
00:23:04,760 --> 00:23:05,920
Grandpa.

293
00:23:06,740 --> 00:23:09,310
Just pick something.
Do whatever works for now.

294
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:10,970
Fine. Fine, I'll do it.

295
00:23:12,560 --> 00:23:13,560
Your phone.

296
00:23:17,190 --> 00:23:18,190
Alright.

297
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:22,640
Right here. Press here.

298
00:23:25,120 --> 00:23:26,680
Hello, check, check.

299
00:23:26,860 --> 00:23:27,860
Done.

300
00:23:29,560 --> 00:23:31,120
"Hello, check, check."

301
00:23:31,120 --> 00:23:33,240
Hey, that's not hard at all.

302
00:23:33,240 --> 00:23:35,440
See? Told you.

303
00:23:36,760 --> 00:23:37,760
What's in that bag?

304
00:23:39,440 --> 00:23:40,440
This?

305
00:23:47,890 --> 00:23:50,320
I'm just...following your advice.

306
00:24:32,460 --> 00:24:33,460
Ow.

307
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:37,920
Ugh, why is this so hard?

308
00:24:41,840 --> 00:24:42,840
Come on.

309
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:05,880
'I'm sorry,'

310
00:25:09,840 --> 00:25:11,040
Somporn says.

311
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:15,040
The guilt was written
all over those eyes.

312
00:25:18,880 --> 00:25:20,080
I'm sorry.

313
00:25:20,360 --> 00:25:21,520
Don't bother.

314
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:25,600
If you meant what you did,
don't apologize.

315
00:25:28,870 --> 00:25:31,420
Man, it was just a moment of anger.

316
00:25:31,820 --> 00:25:34,080
I promise it won't happen again.

317
00:25:42,450 --> 00:25:45,560
I know you like dogs.
Carved this for you all night.

318
00:25:49,430 --> 00:25:50,430
You didn't clean it?

319
00:25:51,180 --> 00:25:53,030
Uhm...I did a little.

320
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:42,520
Not mad anymore?

321
00:26:43,770 --> 00:26:44,770
Still am.

322
00:27:19,560 --> 00:27:23,110
Yo, guys,
any good spot to study tonight?

323
00:27:23,400 --> 00:27:25,560
There's a cafe near my place.
Open 24 hours.

324
00:27:25,560 --> 00:27:26,560
Cool.

325
00:27:28,080 --> 00:27:29,360
Guy, Save, you two coming?

326
00:27:31,570 --> 00:27:34,080
They got into uni already.
They don't care.

327
00:27:34,440 --> 00:27:35,440
Yeah.

328
00:27:36,790 --> 00:27:37,790
I'll go.

329
00:27:39,430 --> 00:27:41,590
Guy, come with us.

330
00:27:44,370 --> 00:27:46,240
I'm busy. You guys go.

331
00:27:49,070 --> 00:27:51,280
Hey, what's going on with you two?

332
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:54,000
Seriously, are you two in a fight?

333
00:27:54,370 --> 00:27:55,370
- No.
- No.

334
00:27:57,830 --> 00:27:58,950
Both of you, come here.

335
00:27:59,690 --> 00:28:01,610
- Get up.
- Come here.

336
00:28:01,630 --> 00:28:02,630
Get up.

337
00:28:07,920 --> 00:28:09,920
Guys, excuse us, please.

338
00:28:23,760 --> 00:28:26,760
Alright, you talk.
We'll handle this.

339
00:28:30,040 --> 00:28:33,360
Dudes, this awkward vibe.
It's killing us.

340
00:28:33,720 --> 00:28:36,280
Any beef between you two,
just let it out. Come on.

341
00:28:38,760 --> 00:28:39,920
Ask Save yourself.

342
00:28:49,100 --> 00:28:51,010
Yeah, I was the one
who made him mad.

343
00:28:51,920 --> 00:28:53,800
When I tried to make up,
he wouldn't.

344
00:28:54,640 --> 00:28:55,680
Try him, will ya?

345
00:28:56,040 --> 00:28:57,280
What did you do to him?

346
00:29:04,740 --> 00:29:06,280
Is it about me teasing you guys?

347
00:29:07,640 --> 00:29:08,640
No.

348
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:10,040
So what is it about then?

349
00:29:19,760 --> 00:29:22,700
Look, if you can't talk
with us around,

350
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:25,000
then just the two of you.

351
00:29:25,960 --> 00:29:28,000
If you can't work it out,
don't come out.

352
00:29:28,820 --> 00:29:29,820
We go, guys.

353
00:29:42,700 --> 00:29:43,880
I've got nothing to say,

354
00:29:46,040 --> 00:29:47,240
except sorry.

355
00:29:48,680 --> 00:29:50,120
That's all you've got?

356
00:29:51,040 --> 00:29:52,560
It's what I genuinely feel.

357
00:30:00,430 --> 00:30:01,430
Guy.

358
00:30:02,520 --> 00:30:04,040
Can we give this another shot?

359
00:30:08,940 --> 00:30:11,720
All this time, you were just
playing around.

360
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:14,040
I was the only one who was serious.

361
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:16,840
I should just let you go.

362
00:30:17,360 --> 00:30:19,000
I don't want to fall any deeper.

363
00:30:52,360 --> 00:30:53,360
Hmm.

364
00:30:57,650 --> 00:30:58,720
Ow.

365
00:31:05,890 --> 00:31:06,890
Oow.

366
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:10,000
Hrr.

367
00:31:13,380 --> 00:31:14,380
Oops.

368
00:31:17,050 --> 00:31:18,050
Hmm.

369
00:31:21,740 --> 00:31:23,160
Hey.

370
00:31:31,180 --> 00:31:32,350
Grr.

371
00:31:34,290 --> 00:31:36,000
Good thing nothing's broken.

372
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:38,080
- Ouch.
- Easy, easy.

373
00:31:38,490 --> 00:31:39,760
Sorry, sorry.

374
00:31:40,380 --> 00:31:41,440
Serves you right.

375
00:31:41,790 --> 00:31:44,120
Told me not to work.

376
00:31:44,510 --> 00:31:50,030
Now you're the one who barely slept.
Dang near wiped out on that bike.

377
00:31:50,250 --> 00:31:51,040
That teach ya?

378
00:31:51,090 --> 00:31:52,960
Aw, Dad.

379
00:31:53,540 --> 00:31:56,560
I've got bones of steel.
Gonna hit me hard to finish me off.

380
00:31:56,610 --> 00:31:57,760
Hehe.

381
00:31:59,430 --> 00:32:00,430
Ow.

382
00:32:01,170 --> 00:32:03,480
Oh. Ow.

383
00:32:03,500 --> 00:32:06,440
Look at this.
We're all down for the count.

384
00:32:07,840 --> 00:32:09,680
Is this a home or a hospital?

385
00:32:12,320 --> 00:32:13,180
Huh.

386
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:16,920
And today Auntie Oui called in
to run some errands.

387
00:32:17,220 --> 00:32:18,360
What do we do now?

388
00:32:26,040 --> 00:32:29,560
Alright. Watch your six.

389
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:31,360
Watch your six.

390
00:32:31,360 --> 00:32:32,360
Be careful.

391
00:32:32,730 --> 00:32:34,280
Hey, food's coming.

392
00:32:35,130 --> 00:32:36,440
Jedi, slow down.

393
00:32:37,670 --> 00:32:38,840
Put them right here.

394
00:32:39,830 --> 00:32:40,830
Whew. That was a workout.

395
00:32:42,230 --> 00:32:43,230
Let's see.

396
00:32:44,230 --> 00:32:47,080
Okay, line up. Quick.

397
00:32:48,980 --> 00:32:49,980
Hmph.

398
00:32:50,960 --> 00:32:51,780
Quick.

399
00:32:51,800 --> 00:32:53,480
- Yeah...
- Get in line.

400
00:33:01,010 --> 00:33:02,990
Okay. Okay.

401
00:33:05,120 --> 00:33:06,360
Pipe, hurry up.

402
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:09,480
- Okay, go.
- Got it.

403
00:33:09,510 --> 00:33:10,640
Just a sec.

404
00:33:11,780 --> 00:33:13,700
Here you go.

405
00:33:13,720 --> 00:33:14,720
Come, come.

406
00:33:15,280 --> 00:33:16,100
Thank you.

407
00:33:16,120 --> 00:33:17,880
Enjoy your meal.

408
00:33:18,160 --> 00:33:21,000
- Please enjoy.
- Thank you.

409
00:33:21,520 --> 00:33:22,560
- Water.
- Get water.

410
00:33:22,810 --> 00:33:26,040
Wow, I wouldn't have guessed

411
00:33:26,420 --> 00:33:28,250
the kids would make
fried rice and egg.

412
00:33:28,520 --> 00:33:29,800
They did.

413
00:33:30,690 --> 00:33:31,900
You didn't help, did you?

414
00:33:31,960 --> 00:33:36,810
How could I?
Even moving hurts right now.

415
00:33:38,120 --> 00:33:43,520
Kids these days are smarter
than we give them credit for.

416
00:33:46,540 --> 00:33:48,200
Yeah, good stuff.

417
00:33:58,320 --> 00:34:01,640
Hi, everyone. Will you throw
this guy some support?

418
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:05,160
With these Sanae Chan sweets,
you're gonna love them.

419
00:34:05,160 --> 00:34:06,200
You won't be disappointed.

420
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:07,760
"Where is Phi Guy?"

421
00:34:10,200 --> 00:34:11,540
Have you ordered yet?

422
00:34:11,780 --> 00:34:13,360
Try one box.

423
00:34:13,960 --> 00:34:15,200
And you'll love them.

424
00:34:20,600 --> 00:34:23,240
And...any questions, just ask.

425
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:27,440
Order now. They look amazing.
Super delicious. I promise.

426
00:35:04,290 --> 00:35:07,040
All this time, you were just
playing around.

427
00:35:07,480 --> 00:35:09,460
I was the only one who was serious.

428
00:35:09,630 --> 00:35:11,050
I think I should just let go.

429
00:35:11,640 --> 00:35:13,240
I don't want to fall any deeper.

430
00:35:40,400 --> 00:35:41,480
Ugh.

431
00:35:58,080 --> 00:36:03,480
Somporn yearned to
make things right with Nan.

432
00:36:04,120 --> 00:36:08,160
Something was slowly taking shape,

433
00:36:08,760 --> 00:36:11,080
like...a whirlpool.

434
00:36:11,720 --> 00:36:15,760
"Even though Nan kept
that cold, stiff wall up,"

435
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:20,460
"in one unguarded moment,"

436
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:23,800
"their eyes locked for just
a fraction of a second,"

437
00:36:24,600 --> 00:36:28,480
"and Somporn knew instantly that..."

438
00:36:29,120 --> 00:36:34,800
"Nan wanted the same thing."

439
00:36:36,560 --> 00:36:39,890
His eyes gave it away.

440
00:36:52,690 --> 00:36:56,240
Hmph.

441
00:37:00,070 --> 00:37:01,070
Grandpa.

442
00:37:12,100 --> 00:37:13,100
Grandpa.

443
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:15,880
Grandpa.

444
00:37:19,520 --> 00:37:20,520
Ow.

445
00:37:49,540 --> 00:37:51,800
- Hello.
- Hello.

446
00:37:52,440 --> 00:37:56,120
Ma'am, these are Sanae Chan sweets
by Auntie Mart.

447
00:37:56,120 --> 00:37:59,240
This is a royal court recipe,
with a Japanese twist,

448
00:37:59,240 --> 00:38:01,000
because it uses mochi flour.

449
00:38:01,130 --> 00:38:04,740
That gives it a chewy texture
unlike anything else.

450
00:38:04,760 --> 00:38:07,840
- They're flying off the shelves.
- Yes.

451
00:38:08,100 --> 00:38:12,500
- If you buy now, you got a three...
- get 1 free deal.

452
00:38:12,500 --> 00:38:15,080
Price? Just as sweet.
Super wallet-friendly.

453
00:38:15,110 --> 00:38:17,390
Just 60 baht a box.

454
00:38:18,320 --> 00:38:19,960
Let's do a taste test.

455
00:38:19,960 --> 00:38:22,060
- 3, 2, 1.
- 3, 2, 1.

456
00:38:22,520 --> 00:38:23,520
Ting.

457
00:38:24,520 --> 00:38:25,960
- Yum.
- Oh.

458
00:38:26,600 --> 00:38:30,040
- So good. Unbelievable texture.
- Soft and chewy like a dream.

459
00:38:30,040 --> 00:38:31,560
Nothing else comes close.

460
00:38:57,720 --> 00:38:58,720
Come in.

461
00:39:05,880 --> 00:39:07,040
Here you go.

462
00:39:41,190 --> 00:39:42,720
"5"

463
00:40:40,280 --> 00:40:42,210
"Between Us in the Deep Forest"

464
00:40:42,210 --> 00:40:43,840
Give it a read for me.

465
00:41:05,760 --> 00:41:09,080
"Lacerating yearn" means what?

466
00:41:10,160 --> 00:41:11,440
You don't know that word?

467
00:41:12,560 --> 00:41:14,120
Tell us, Director.

468
00:41:14,400 --> 00:41:15,600
It means what, Grandpa?

469
00:41:18,560 --> 00:41:21,120
Simply put, it means
to miss someone.

470
00:41:21,340 --> 00:41:24,240
But on a deeper level.

471
00:41:24,560 --> 00:41:25,240
Hmm?

472
00:41:25,240 --> 00:41:27,040
So deep it burns.

473
00:41:27,040 --> 00:41:27,960
- Woo.
-Hoo.

474
00:41:27,960 --> 00:41:29,720
Wanting to see that face every day.

475
00:41:29,720 --> 00:41:30,720
- Heh.
- Sweet.

476
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:35,280
Wanting to hold them,
wanting them near always.

477
00:41:35,280 --> 00:41:37,080
- Argh.
- Raah.

478
00:41:38,150 --> 00:41:41,400
Yes, you've hit the sweet spot.
Perfect.

479
00:41:41,480 --> 00:41:42,200
Yes.

480
00:41:42,200 --> 00:41:45,640
I love it so much, Grandpa.
Is there more? Please, please.

481
00:41:45,920 --> 00:41:47,120
Yes.

482
00:41:48,140 --> 00:41:49,320
I need to read more.

483
00:41:55,920 --> 00:41:58,280
So? Fun, right?

484
00:41:58,880 --> 00:41:59,960
So much fun, sir.

485
00:42:00,400 --> 00:42:03,160
So your publishing house
will print it for me?

486
00:42:04,440 --> 00:42:06,800
Yes, the writing is beautiful.

487
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:07,360
Mm-hmm.

488
00:42:07,360 --> 00:42:08,880
- The style is great.
- Yes.

489
00:42:09,210 --> 00:42:11,120
But it's a bit much
for young readers.

490
00:42:11,530 --> 00:42:12,530
Not at all.

491
00:42:12,760 --> 00:42:16,000
The kids at my place read it
and all understood it fine.

492
00:42:16,600 --> 00:42:20,640
And to make sure,
we can explain in footnotes.

493
00:42:20,780 --> 00:42:24,520
So readers who don't know
the vocabulary can learn as they go.

494
00:42:26,520 --> 00:42:27,720
Here's the thing, sir.

495
00:42:28,000 --> 00:42:30,720
I'm not saying
it's not a good novel.

496
00:42:31,880 --> 00:42:35,120
But I'm not sure it'll sell
in the current market.

497
00:42:35,120 --> 00:42:38,080
I think it's a bit niche.
It's not...quite mass.

498
00:42:38,600 --> 00:42:39,600
Mass?

499
00:42:40,120 --> 00:42:42,000
Meaning it won't appeal to many.

500
00:42:43,080 --> 00:42:46,840
And like I mentioned before,
it needs NC scenes.

501
00:42:47,720 --> 00:42:50,960
But yours maxes out at a hug.

502
00:42:52,610 --> 00:42:53,610
Hmm.

503
00:42:54,960 --> 00:42:56,240
My suggestion, sir.

504
00:42:56,980 --> 00:43:00,200
Maybe try submitting it
elsewhere first.

505
00:43:00,560 --> 00:43:01,800
I'm rooting for you.

506
00:43:37,720 --> 00:43:38,760
Huh.

507
00:43:41,520 --> 00:43:45,320
It's okay, Grandpa.
They can't see it, but I can.

508
00:43:49,720 --> 00:43:51,400
We don't need a publisher anymore.

509
00:43:53,240 --> 00:43:54,240
I have a way.

510
00:43:57,210 --> 00:44:00,360
These days,
people post novels online.

511
00:44:00,960 --> 00:44:02,320
People publish on their own.

512
00:44:02,320 --> 00:44:04,440
You can do an e-book
or a print copy.

513
00:44:05,480 --> 00:44:06,880
Does that cost a lot?

514
00:44:07,020 --> 00:44:10,520
Posting online is free.

515
00:44:11,360 --> 00:44:14,160
But if you want a print copy,
I will chip in.

516
00:44:15,830 --> 00:44:16,920
You have money?

517
00:44:17,200 --> 00:44:20,420
Sold some game accounts.
Got a decent amount.

518
00:44:20,440 --> 00:44:24,600
You actually make money
tapping on your phone all day?

519
00:44:24,600 --> 00:44:26,600
Hmm, not bad, huh?

520
00:44:27,850 --> 00:44:31,800
But...how can I take your money?

521
00:44:31,800 --> 00:44:32,800
No.

522
00:44:33,690 --> 00:44:37,800
Grandpa, I want to use it
to help our family.

523
00:44:42,690 --> 00:44:45,150
Oh, don't cry.

524
00:44:46,400 --> 00:44:48,640
Ooh...I'm not crying.

525
00:44:52,140 --> 00:44:53,140
Now.

526
00:44:54,000 --> 00:44:55,000
Here.

527
00:44:57,600 --> 00:45:01,000
And Grandpa, I paid someone
to design a cover.

528
00:45:01,780 --> 00:45:02,840
Nice, isn't it?

529
00:45:03,440 --> 00:45:04,920
- Really nice.
- Mm-hmm.

530
00:45:05,660 --> 00:45:07,860
And if I upload this now,

531
00:45:08,240 --> 00:45:10,240
by tomorrow, it may be out. Perfect.

532
00:45:10,240 --> 00:45:12,640
It's a holiday.
People will have time to read.

533
00:45:14,970 --> 00:45:18,010
So...what pen name do you want?

534
00:45:18,760 --> 00:45:19,800
Harn Chanprai?

535
00:45:19,830 --> 00:45:21,350
Hmm? No, no.

536
00:45:22,560 --> 00:45:23,920
Then what?

537
00:45:24,600 --> 00:45:26,690
Anything. Help me think of one.

538
00:45:27,350 --> 00:45:29,880
Something people won't
trace back to me.

539
00:46:02,200 --> 00:46:03,200
Yeah.

540
00:46:03,560 --> 00:46:05,440
Save, get over here now. Right now.

541
00:46:06,190 --> 00:46:07,190
What's going on?

542
00:46:08,200 --> 00:46:09,400
Guy's leaving today.

543
00:46:09,770 --> 00:46:12,760
Today? Why? Where's he going?

544
00:46:14,380 --> 00:46:16,920
America on an athletic scholarship.

545
00:46:17,480 --> 00:46:19,720
We're at the school field.
Get here fast.

546
00:46:27,800 --> 00:46:30,160
Grandpa, I have to run.

547
00:46:30,560 --> 00:46:31,720
Have Snow come help, okay?

548
00:46:32,240 --> 00:46:33,240
Okay?

549
00:46:48,530 --> 00:46:49,530
Ow.

550
00:46:52,760 --> 00:46:55,350
